Durban -  A man who allegedly killed a woman by slitting her throat and setting her home on fire handed himself over to Phoenix police earlier today. Phoenix mother of two Alvina Singh, 40, was found dead in the bedroom of her home in Stonebridge, Phoenix on Friday morning. Singh sustained an open wound across her neck and severe burn wounds to her body. Her body had been covered with a duvet. According to a source who is not authorised to speak to the media, a 40 year old man known to the victim, handed himself over to the Durban North SAPS on Monday "The suspect was on the run has now been detained at the Phoenix Police for questioning." Glen Naidoo, a spokesperson for private security company KwaZulu- Natal VIP Unit, said when reaction officers arrived on scene they found the windows were closed and doors were locked. "The interior of the house was filled with black smoke. Members were forced to break the door to find the source of the fire and extinguish it,” said Naidoo. “Officers suspected foul play. They found blood stains inside the house. A search revealed the body of a woman in one of the rooms,” said Naidoo. Police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said a case of murder and arson has been opened. POST